INDICATOR_NAME: Population ages 65 and above (% of total)
SOURCE_NOTE: Population ages 65 and above as a percentage of the total population. Population is based on the de facto definition of population, which counts all residents regardless of legal status or citizenship--except for refugees not permanently settled in the country of asylum, who are generally considered part of the population of the country of origin.
SOURCE_ORGANIZATION: The United Nations Population Division's World Population Prospects.
